@@TJvDateTimePicker.DropDownDate
Summary
  Indicates the initial date to display when the calendar illustration is shown and Date or Time equals
  NullDate.
Description
  Use DropDownDate to specify an initial date that is shown in the drop-down calendar illustration,
  when Date or Time - depending on the Kind property - equals NullDate.
  
  For example, if Kind is set to dtkDate, Date and NullDate are set to 1-1-2000, DropDownDate 
  is set to 2-2-2002 and NullDate equals '(None)', then the text '(None)' is shown in the edit box. 
  If the user drops down the calendar illustration then the date 2-2-2002 is highlighted.
